implement this change so that PDFs can be viewed on the web platform:
The message "React Native WebView does not support this platform" indicates that you are attempting to use the react-native-webview component in an environment where it is not designed to run, most commonly when targeting web platforms with React Native for Web.
Explanation and Solution:
The react-native-webview library provides a WebView component for displaying web content within native mobile applications (iOS and Android). It leverages the native WebView components available on those platforms.
When developing for web platforms using React Native for Web, the WebView component from react-native-webview is not compatible because web browsers already have the capability to display web content directly.
To resolve this, you need to implement platform-specific code:
Detect the platform: Use Platform.OS from react-native to determine if the application is running on a web platform.
Render an iframe for web: If Platform.OS === 'web', render a standard HTML iframe element to display the web content.
Render WebView for native: If Platform.OS is 'ios' or 'android', render the WebView component from react-native-webview.
Example:
JavaScript

import React from 'react';
import { Platform } from 'react-native';
import { WebView } from 'react-native-webview'; // Only for native platforms

interface CustomWebViewProps {
  uri: string;
}

export const CustomWebView: React.FC<CustomWebViewProps> = ({ uri }) => {
  if (Platform.OS === 'web') {
    // Render an iframe for web platforms
    return (
      <iframe
        src={uri}
        style={{ width: '100%', height: '100%', border: 'none' }}
        title="Web Content"
      />
    );
  } else {
    // Render WebView for native platforms (iOS/Android)
    return <WebView source={{ uri }} style={{ flex: 1 }} />;
  }
};
